  "prompt": "What should I wear when I make American Girl doll tube tops and skirts out of socks?",
  "response": "When making American Girl doll tube tops and skirts out of socks, it's best to wear something comfortable and practical. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. **Casual Top**: Wear a simple t-shirt or tank top that you don\u2019t mind getting threads or fabric paint on, if you plan to use any.\n\n2. **Comfortable Bottoms**: Opt for loose-fitting pants or shorts. Leggings or joggers are great choices because they offer flexibility and comfort.\n\n3. **Apron**: If you're using scissors or fabric glue, consider wearing an apron to protect your clothes.\n\n4. **Closed-Toe Shoes**: Wear comfortable shoes, ideally closed-toe, to protect your feet while you\u2019re working.\n\n5. **Accessories**: Keep your hair tied back if it\u2019s long, and you might want to wear gloves if you're handling any fabrics that could irritate your skin.\n\nOverall, the key is to choose clothing that allows you to move freely and protects you from any crafting mess!",
